just_use pair_peel.go

# label: INTRICATE
# role: encodes domain knowledge

"Two hand cards form a pair, peel a board card to complete the triplet."
Three pair kinds handled by pairNeeds:

- Set pair (same value, different suits) — need any of the remaining two
  suits at that value.
- Pure-run pair (consecutive same-suit) — need predecessor OR successor in
  the same suit.
- Rb-run pair (consecutive alternating color) — need predecessor OR
  successor in the opposite color's two suits.

Peel target must pass CanExtract. On Apply, sorts the trio by value
before pushing so the new stack reads naturally, plus a belt-and-braces
GetStackType check (Bogus/Dup/Incomplete rejected).
